overview: "The user initiated a request to fix a pull request riddled with
  issues, ranging from critical security vulnerabilities to functional bugs and
  persistent Vercel deployment failures. The agent systematically addressed each
  concern. This included overhauling the authentication system to use secure
  HMAC-based sessions compatible with Vercel's Edge Runtime, implementing robust
  validation for API parameters, and optimizing CSV exports to prevent memory
  exhaustion. Key bugs in PDF generation, number input fields, and UI
  interactivity were also resolved. The debugging process for Vercel deployments
  was iterative: initially, lint errors were found to be locally resolved.
  Subsequent failures were traced to a missing database URL in the Prisma
  schema, then to a critical Next.js security vulnerability (CVE-2025-66478)
  that necessitated an update. This update, in turn, introduced breaking changes
  in Prisma 7, requiring a further adjustment to the Prisma schema. The codebase
  was thoroughly updated and refactored, leading to a successful local build and
  GitHub Actions CI. The final Vercel deployment was still awaiting external
  environment variable configuration by the user."
